pean Union]]\n[[Category:People associated with transport in London]]\n[[Category:Political sex scandals in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:English magazine editors]]\n[[Category:The Spectator editors]]\n[[Category:Daily Telegraph journalists]]\n[[Category:The Times people]]\n[[Category:20th-century British journalists]]\n[[Category:21st-century British journalists]]\n[[Category:English political writers]]\n[[Category:English male non-fiction writers]]\n[[Category:Writers from London]]\n[[Category:20th-century English writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century English writers]]\n[[Category:American magazine editors]]\n[[Category:American political writers]]\n[[Category:American male writers]]\n[[Category:20th-century American journalists]]\n[[Category:21st-century American journalists]]\n[[Category:People who lost United States citizenship]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Balliol College, Oxford]]\n[[Category:Presidents of the Oxford Union]]\n[[Category:People educated at Ashdown House]]\n[[Category:People educated at Eton College]]\n[[Category:English Anglicans]]\n[[Category:American Anglicans]]\n[[Category:20th-century Anglicans]]\n[[Category:21st-century Anglicans]]\n[[Category:Converts to Anglicanism from Roman Catholicism]]\n[[Category:Christians from Connecticut]]\n[[Category:Christians from New York (state)]]\n[[Category:English people of American descent]]\n[[Category:American people of English descent]]\n[[Category:People from Crouch End]]\n[[Category:People from Maida Vale]]\n[[Category:People from Uccle]]\n[[Category:Politicians from Norwalk, Connecticut]]\n[[Category:Writers from Norwalk, Connecticut]]\n[[Category:Politicians from New York City]]\n[[Category:Writers from New York City]]\n[[Category:People from the Upper East Side]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 2019\u2013]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the European Schools]]\n", "name_user": "DonSpencer1", "label": "safe", "comment": "Link and dates", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boris_Johnson"}
{"title_page": "Everytime (Ariana Grande song)", "text_new": "{{short description|2018 song by Ariana Grande}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name     = Everytime\n| cover    =\n| alt      =\n| type     =song\n| artist   = [[Ariana Grande]]\n| album    = [[Sweetener (album)|Sweetener]]\n| released = August 17, 2018\n| format   =* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n* [[streaming media|streaming]]\n| recorded = 2017\n| studio   = \n| venue    =\n| genre    = \n*[[Trap music|Trap]]-[[Pop music|pop]]\n*[[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]<ref name=\"sterogum\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.stereogum.com/2010700/ariana-grande-sweetener-review/franchises/premature-evaluation/|title=Premature Evaluation: Ariana Grande 'Sweetener'|date=2018-08-20|work=Stereogum|access-date=2018-11-17|quote=The downbeat but booming \u201cEverytime,\u201d a wispy \u201990s R&B song reimagined for the trap era [...] The brokenhearted trap-pop aesthetic definitely manifests on the sparkling Max Martin and Ilya production \u201cEverytime}}</ref>\n| length   = 2:52\n| label    =\n|writer= {{Flatlist|\n* [[Ariana Grande]]\n* [[Ilya Salmanzadeh]]\n* [[Savan Kotecha]]\n* [[Max Martin]]\n}}\n| producer = {{flatlist|\n* Max Martin\n* Ilya\n}}\n| misc     = {{External music video|1={{YouTube|MYvjW3zdCws|\"Everytime\"}}|header=Audio video|type=song}}\n}}\n\n\"'''Everytime'''\" (stylized in all lower-case) is a song by American singer [[Ariana Grande]] from her fourth studio album ''[[Sweetener (album)|Sweetener]]'', released in 2018. The song was written by Grande, [[Savan Kotecha]] and its producers [[Max Martin]] and [[Ilya Salmanzadeh]].\n\n== Development and composition ==\n[[Rolling Stone]]'s Elias Leight noted \"At first Grande delivers an unyielding staccato rap, but she abruptly returns to supple singing on the line-ending phrase \u201cback to you;\u201d the effect is like a boxer following a series of short jabs with an uppercut. As more and more pop singers are forced to reckon with trap, the fusion achieved on \u201cEverytime\u201d offers them a path forward.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/ariana-grandes-sweetener-proves-that-trap-is-the-new-pop-712838/|title=Ariana Grande\u2019s \u2018Sweetener\u2019 Proves That Trap Is the New Pop|last=Leight|first=Elias|date=2018-08-17|work=Rolling Stone|access-date=2018-11-17|language=en-US}}</ref> Lyrically, Grande sings about being in a toxic relationship with an ex and how she couldn't get over someone even though she knew it was unhealthy to stay involved.<ref name=\"vulture\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.vulture.com/2018/08/maybe-everytime-should-be-ariana-grandes-next-single.html|title=Maybe \u2018Everytime\u2019 Should Be Ariana Grande\u2019s Next Single|last=Hockley-Smith|first=Sam|date=2018-08-17|work=Vulture|access-date=2019-12-31|language=en-US}}</ref><ref name=\"elite\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.elitedaily.com/p/is-ariana-grandes-everytime-about-mac-miller-the-lyrics-blast-a-toxic-ex-10132321|title=Is Ariana Grande's \"Everytime\" About Mac Miller? The Lyrics Blast A Toxic Ex|last=Martinez|first=Tara|date=2018-08-17|work=Elite Daily|access-date=2019-12-31|language=en-US}}</ref> She expresses feelings of desire and frustration in equal measure and the song makes references to drugs and alcohol,<ref name=\"vulture\" /><ref name=\"spin\" /> leading some fans to speculate that the song alludes to Grande's past relationship with rapper [[Mac Miller]].<ref name=\"elite\" />\n\nIn his review, Taylor Weatherby of ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' called the song an \"upbeat\" track.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8470799/ariana-grande-sweetener-uplifting-review|title=6 Reasons Ariana Grande's 'Sweetener' Is Her Most Uplifting Album Yet|work=Billboard|access-date=2018-11-17}}</ref> In August 2018, Grande shared on social media behind-the-scenes footage from the song's recording session in which she laughs while she is singing in reaction to Max Martin's inability to keep a straight face.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8470866/ariana-grande-sweetener-behind-the-scenes-video-everytime|title=Ariana Grande Shares 'Sweetener' Studio Footage of Her Genuine 'Everytime' Giggle: Watch|last=Hughes|first=Hilary|date=2018-08-18|work=Billboard|access-date=2019-12-31|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n== Critical reception ==\nBrittany Spanos of ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' called the song a \"gorgeous, self-reflective break-up ballad\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-album-reviews/review-ariana-grande-finds-serenity-and-has-some-fun-on-sweetener-713404/|title=Review: Ariana Grande Finds Serenity and Has Some Fun on \u2018 Sweetener\u2019|last=Spanos|first=Brittany|date=2018-08-20|work=Rolling Stone|access-date=2018-11-17|language=en-US}}</ref> [[Stereogum]]'s Chris DeVile noted \"The brokenhearted trap-pop aesthetic definitely manifests on the sparkling Max Martin and Ilya production\".<ref name=\"sterogum\"/> In his review of the song, Israel Daramola of ''[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]'' wrote: \"The best pop songs about love make you want to be in it, or remember it, or make you feel like you\u2019re experiencing it, all of which is provoked at the onset of 'everytime's' twinkling production.\" Daramola also complimented Grande's \"pristine\" vocals and her relatable, convincing emotions.<ref name=\"spin\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.spin.com/2018/08/ariana-grande-everytime-review/|title=Ariana Grande\u2019s \u201cEverytime\u201d Is Pure Pop Bliss |last=Daramola|first=Israel|date=2018-08-20|work=Spin|access-date=2019-12-31|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n== Credits and personnel ==\nCredits adapted from [[Tidal (service)|Tidal]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://listen.tidal.com/album/93686128|title=Try the TIDAL Web Player|website=listen.tidal.com|language=en|access-date=2019-06-24}}</ref>\n\n* [[Ariana Grande]] \u2013 vocals, songwriter\n* [[Max Martin]] \u2013 producer, songwriter, programmer, bass, drums\n* [[Ilya Salmanzadeh]] \u2013 producer, songwriter, programmer, bass, drums\n* [[Savan Kotecha]] \u2013 songwriter\n* Sam Holland \u2013 recording engineer, studio personnel\n* Cory Bice \u2013 assistant recording engineer, studio personnel\n* Jeremy Lertola \u2013 assistant recording engineer, studio personnel\n* Serban Ghenea \u2013 mixer, studio personnel\n* John Hanes \u2013 mix engineer, studio personnel\n\n== Live performances ==\nGrande debuted the song live at [[The Sweetener Sessions]].{{cn|date=November 2018}}\nGrande performed a shortened version of the song at her [[Sweetener World Tour]] in 2019.\n\n== Charts ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2018)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{single chart|Australia|36|artist=Ariana Grande|song=Everytime|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 16, 2019}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Canada|51|artist=Ariana Grande|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 16, 2019}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Hungary ([[Association of Hungarian Record Companies|Single Top 40]])<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://zene.slagerlistak.hu/single-track-top-40-lista/2018/34|title=Single (track) Top 40 lista - Hivatalos magyar sl\u00e1gerlist\u00e1k|website=zene.slagerlistak.hu|access-date=2018-11-16}}</ref>\n| 12\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Hungary ([[Association of Hungarian Record Companies|Stream Top 40]])<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://zene.slagerlistak.hu/stream-top-40-slagerlista/2018/34|title=Stream Top 40 sl\u00e1gerlista - Hivatalos magyar sl\u00e1gerlist\u00e1k|website=zene.slagerlistak.hu|access-date=2019-02-08}}</ref>\n| 30\n|-\n{{single chart|Dutch100|85|artist=Ariana Grande|song=Everytime|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 16, 2019}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| New Zealand Hot Singles ([[Recorded Music NZ]])<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nztop40.co.nz/chart/hotsingles?chart=4517|title=NZ Hot Singles|publisher=[[Recorded Music NZ]]|access-date=2018-11-16}}</ref>\n| 4\n|-\n{{single chart|Portu