|3}}\n| Aux3 = [[Beijing]], [[China]]\n| ShortSummary = The kids plan a special day for Luna, coincidentally on the same day as the traditional [[Mid-Autumn Festival|Moon Festival]] in [[China]].<hr>Honey is feeling bored of her old cage and wants her new one to be a [[Chinese drum]].\n| LineColor = 3198FF\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 8\n| Title = Hoopin' Hopper\"<hr>\"A Chopsticky Situation\n| WrittenBy = Mark Haslett<hr>Peter Hannan\n| Aux2 = Dan Becker & Eric David Haddad<hr>Tom Smith & Jackie Bae\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|12|4}}\n| Aux3 = [[Beijing]], [[China]]\n| ShortSummary = Andy loses his basketball in [[Beijing]], and through playing more sports to retrieve it, learns that friendship is much more important than winning.<hr>Leo has a difficult time learning to eat with [[chopsticks]] at a [[Chinese restaurant]].\n| LineColor = 3198FF\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 9\n| Title = Speaking Wigglewalker\"<hr>\"London Frog\n| WrittenBy = Peter Hannan<hr>Mark Haslett\n| Aux2 = Dan Becker & Eric David Haddad<hr>Tom Smith & Jackie Bae\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|11|21}}<hr>{{Start date|2018|12|11}}\n| Aux3 = [[London]], [[United Kingdom]]\n| ShortSummary = Andy is confused during a trip to a [[London]] supermarket due to the differences between [[British English]] and [[American English]].<hr>Luna helps the kids navigate the London fog to find [[Big Ben]].\n| LineColor = 3198FF\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 10\n| Title = Queen for a Day\"<hr>\"Jolly Special Friend\n| WrittenBy = Rachel Lipman<hr>Joe Murray\n| Aux2 = Dan Becker & Eric David Haddad<hr>Tom Smith & Jackie Bae\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|12|13}}\n| Aux3 = [[London]], [[United Kingdom]]\n| ShortSummary = Carmen pretends to be the Queen of [[Buckingham Palace]], but later finds it less fun than she imagined.<hr>Papa Chockers is too sick to make lunch for Se\u00f1or Fabuloso's friend so Leo and his friends go out to get some [[multiculturalism|traditional]] London food for them.\n| LineColor = 3198FF\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 11\n| Title = Guitar to Sitar\"<hr>\"Spring Has Not Sprung\n| WrittenBy = Mark Haslett<hr>Peter Hannan\n| Aux2 = Dan Becker & Eric David Haddad<hr>Jackie Bae & Tom Smith\n| Aux3 = [[Delhi]], [[India]]\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|03|04}}\n| ShortSummary = The strings on Carmen's guitar snap while she is writing a song for her mother's birthday and she needs to buy more from the bazaar.<hr>Andy wants to photograph the Springtime colors of Dehli but then an overcast weather turns everything gray.\n| LineColor = 3198FF\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 12\n| Title = Where's Luna?\"<hr>\"Pulling Strings\n| WrittenBy = Joe Murray<hr>Rachel Lipman\n| Aux2 =Jackie Bae & Dan Becker<hr>Eric David Haddad & Tom Smith\n| Aux3 = [[Delhi]], [[India]]\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|03|05}}\n| ShortSummary = Luna appears to have gone missing so the Trio, along with Se\u00f1or Fabuloso, try and find her.<hr>Andy and Carmen get into an argument and stop talking to each other, so Luna and Leo try to use a traditional [[Kathputli (Puppet)|Kathputli]] puppet show to help them make up.\n| LineColor = 3198FF\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 13\n| Title = Didgeridoo and Carmen Too\"<hr>\"Not Home on the Range\n| WrittenBy = Rachel Lipman<hr>Peter Hannan\n| Aux2 = Dan Becker & Eric David Haddad<hr>Tom Smith & Jackie Bae\n| Aux3 = [[Sydney]], [[Australia]]\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|03|06}}\n| ShortSummary = Carmen borrows a [[didgeridoo]] from a new friend in [[Sydney]] but ends up losing it, so she tries to make a new one.<hr>A visit to his uncle's [[cattle station]] forces Leo to confront his [[equinophobia|fear of horses]].\n| LineColor = 3198FF\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 14\n| Title =Boomin' Boomerang\"<hr>\"House Music\n| WrittenBy = Joe Murray<hr>Mark Haslett\n| Aux2 = Dan Becker & Eric David Haddad<hr>Tom Smith & Jackie Bae\n| Aux3 = [[Sydney]], [[Australia]]\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|03|07}}\n| ShortSummary = Carmen is asked to compete in a [[boomerang]] throwing competition but she lacks confidence.<hr>Andy is excited to hear the band Syd and the Sydneys perform at the [[Sydney Opera House]].\n| LineColor = 3198FF\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 15\n| Title =You Can't Move the Moon\"<hr>\"Lizardzilla!\n| WrittenBy = Mark Haslett<hr>Peter Hannan\n| Aux2 = Dan Becker & Eric David Haddad<hr>Tom Smith & Jackie Bae\n| Aux3 = [[Tokyo]], [[Japan]]\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|05|27}}\n| ShortSummary = A [[sumo|Sumo wrestler]] puts on an exhibition match with Luna after Salami Strong gets injured.<hr>Leo is too afraid to watch a Lizardzilla movie, but becomes less afraid when he sees how the [[kaiju|movies]] are made.\n| LineColor = 3198FF\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 16\n| Title =Windy Washi\"<hr>\"When the Bowl Breaks\n| WrittenBy = Joe Murray<hr>Rachel Lipman\n| Aux2 = Dan Becker & Eric David Haddad<hr>Tom Smith & Jackie Bae\n| Aux3 = [[Tokyo]], [[Japan]]\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|05|28}}\n| ShortSummary = Andy is asked to make posters for the Circo, which leads to learning about the many uses of [[washi paper]].<hr>Leo learns how to [[kintsugi|repair broken pottery]] after he accidentally breaks his dad's [[chawan|special tea bowl]].\n| LineColor = 3198FF\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 17\n| Title = A Prickly Pair\"<hr>\"Turkish Delight\n| WrittenBy = Peter Hannan<hr>Mark Haslett\n| Aux2 = Dan Becker & Eric David Haddad<hr>Tom Smith & Keith Silva\n| Aux3 = [[Istanbul]], [[Turkey]]\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|07|22}}\n| ShortSummary = In Istanbul, Carmen is excited to see the juggling act \"The Prickly Brothers\" perform, but the two are feuding.<hr>After a firefighter rescues his pet tortoise from a tree, Leo wants to thank him by making him some [[Turkish Delight]], but his unwillingness to pay attention causes trouble.\n| LineCo