hods of farming as well as Luna's unique methods of harvesting.\n| LineColor = 3198FF\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 30\n| Title = Beat the Beat\"<hr>\"Rhinoceros or Bust\n| WrittenBy =Peter Hannan\n| Aux2 =Dan Becker & Ben Fossleman<hr>Tom Smith & Keith Silva\n| Aux3 = [[Nairobi]], [[Kenya]]\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|2|15}} (Canada)<br>{{Start date|2020|5|20}} (USA)\n| ShortSummary = Everyone in the Circo is having a miserable day, so the kids and Luna seek out a [[Benga music|Benga]] band to cheer everyone up.<hr>Andy wants to a picture of a rhinoceros for his scrapbook, so Luna takes him on a photo safari at [[Nairobi National Park]].\n| LineColor = 3198FF\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 31<ref>This episode does not follow the standard \"Two episodes per location\" format, being the only episode thus far to take place here.</ref>\n| Title = More Than All That Jazz\"<hr>\"Swamp Pals\n| WrittenBy = Peter Hannan<hr>Luccy Baillie\n| Aux2 = Dan Becker & Ben Fosselman<hr>Keith Silva & Kathy Jo Larson\n| Aux3 = [[New Orleans]], [[Louisiana]]\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|2|6}} (USA)<br>{{Start date|2020|3|22}} (Canada)\n| ShortSummary = Carmen puts together a jazz band with Leo and Andy to take the place of the Circo's band, but they aren't very good until they're taught about [[jazz improvisation]].<hr>Leo is nervous to meet his pen pal Remy in the Louisiana [[bayou]] because of how amazing he made it sound in his letters.\n| LineColor = 3198FF\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 32\n| Title = Blue Orleans\"<hr>\"Bonjour, Au Revoir, Adios\n| WrittenBy = Peter Hannan & Luccy Baillie<hr>Peter Hannan\n| Aux2 = Dan Becker & Ben Fossleman<hr>Tom Smith & Keith Sliva\n| Aux3 = [[New Orleans]], [[Louisiana]]\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|21}} (Canada)<br>{{Start date|2020|5|22}} (USA)\n| ShortSummary =\n| LineColor = 3198FF\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 33\n| Title = The Potato King\"<hr>\"The Charango Kid\n| WrittenB